AWS lambda offers  maintenance-free and highly available computing environment. You create function, upload codes and configure the execute environment. Then. AWS
will take care of it.

Languages supported:  Java, Go, PowerShell, Node.js, C#, Python, and Ruby


How to invoke lambda function:

1. create a scheduled event rule. Let it run like a cron job

2. consume by AWS api gateway (AWS API gateway to Lambda)
User call the aws api gateway as a rest api call (can do no rest favor). api gateway send request to lambda function.
Post body will be events parameter of a Lambda function.

This is link for a good tutorial about this option 2.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uFsaiEhr1zs



